Close Brace 5 Minute React: ESLint

  Code Consistency

  ---------
  Resources
  ---------

    JavaScript Style Guide - AirBnB: https://github.com/airbnb/javascript

  --------
  Commands
  --------

    Find all files with linting errors: $ yarn lint

  -------
  Install
  -------

    $ npm info "eslint-config-airbnb@latest" peerDependencies. // Get current versions of dependencies


    Replace versions with current and install with yarn

      $ yarn add --dev eslint-config-airbnb eslint@^4.9.0 eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y@^6.0.2 eslint-plugin-import@^2.7.0 eslint-plugin-react@^7.4.0

    Create a text file in top level of app called: .eslintrc 

    Add the following to .eslintrc:

      {
        "extends": "airbnb"
      }

    Save & Close any open .js files

    Add rule exception for including next without explicitly using it:

    {
      "extends": "airbnb",
      "rules": {
        "no-unused-vars": ["error", { "argsIgnorePattern": "next" }]
      }
    }

    Install ESLint and its dependencies globally in order to run from command line:

      $ yarn global add eslint-config-airbnb eslint@^4.9.0 eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y@^6.0.2 eslint-plugin-import@^2.7.0 eslint-plugin-react@^7.4.0

    Add plugin to lint jest tests:

      $ yarn add --dev eslint-plugin-jest
      $ yarn global add eslint-plugin-jest

    Edit .eslintrc (add the following below the "extends" block but above the "rules" block:

      "plugins": [ "jest" ],
      "env": {
        "jest/globals": true
      }

    Setup a script to run the linter:

      Open package.json and add to the scripts section:

        "lint": "eslint ."


